qas.question: What is the Russian term for prime minister?
What is the Israeli term for prime minister?
What is the term used in spain for prime minister?

answers.text: President of the Government (Presidente del Gobierno)

qas.question: What is the Irish term for prime minister?
Who is Chairmen of the government in Ireland?
What is another termfor Rosh HaMemshalah in Russia?

context: In the Russian constitution the <b5_0>prime minister<b5_0/> is actually titled <a0_0>Chairman of the government<a0_0/> while the Irish <b4_0>prime minister<b4_0/> is called the <a3_0>Taoiseach<a3_0/> (which is rendered into English as prime minister), and in Israel he is <a1_0>Rosh HaMemshalah<a1_0/> meaning "head of the government". In many cases, though commonly used, "prime minister" is not the official title of the office-holder; the Spanish prime minister is the <a2_0>President of the Government (Presidente del Gobierno)<a2_0/>.
